{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43dcb7ed-a49e-499b-bcb2-8fdbc6412179","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (recommended for .NET apps):\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-your.dmp>\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` (printexception) — last exception details\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**Using `lldb` (Linux) or WinDbg (Windows)** for deeper native analysis.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file and I'll walk through it interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d4bde73d-5f01-4ec5-b5e0-c565c9e8890b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to analyze a .dmp crash dump file from their .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nInstead, I'll provide guidance on how to analyze the dump file directly.","outputTokens":335,"requestId":"C3D1:2A497:1CA25A5:2047C8E:6A07C3AD"},"id":"117de3bb-5720-42e9-b419-afde6cb463b1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:09:10.738Z","parentId":"3dd8a267-00df-46eb-b5ae-06fad1800188"}
